guaranty funds 
under state insurance guaranty fund laws  insurers doing business in a state can be assessed  up to prescribed limits  in order to cover certain obligations of insolvent insurance companies 
national flood insurance program 
we voluntarily participate as a write your own carrier in the national flood insurance program nfip 
the nfip is administered and regulated by the federal emergency management agency 
we operate as a fiscal agent of the federal government in the selling and administering of the standard flood insurance policy 
this involves the collection of premiums belonging to the federal government and the paying of covered claims by directly drawing on funds of the united states treasury 
we receive expense allowances from the nfip for underwriting administration  claims management  commissions and adjuster fees 
